page.title: 11Lifestyle Of A Boy
page.content: My radio wakes me up for my morning paper round.About 6.20 I arrive at the newsagents and start my round.After this I will have my breakfast and get ready for school. I catch the bus to the Ramsey Ailwyn at about 8.20a.m. and we arrive at 8.55a.m.There are 8 lessons in the day and always consist of at least one lesson of maths and one lesson of english.The bell for end of school rings at 4.00 O'clock.When I get home, I have a packet of crisps and a drink and watch television. Later on I have my tea which usually consists of meat and potatoes and a vegetable.After I go out,I do my homework or watch television.It varies on what time I go to bed depending on whats on television. By { Jeremy Costello {
